{"title_page": "SIN R1", "text_new": "{{One source|date=May 2017}}\n\n[[File:Sin R1 at Goodwood 2014 004.jpg|thumb|Sin R1]]\n\nThe '''SIN R1''' is a [[sports car]] made by Bulgarian manufacturers [[SIN Cars]]. FIA certified tube frame construction, carbon fiber body and an active rear spoiler. It came with a 3 different engine choices \u2013 [[LS based GM small-block engine|LS3]] (6.2 liter N/A V8), [[LS based GM small-block engine|LS7]] (7.0 liter N/A V8) and a [[LS based GM small-block engine|LS9]] (6.2 liter supercharged V8). The only transmission offered is a 6 speed manual. The car weighs just 1250&nbsp;kg (2 755&nbsp;lbs) and has a top speed of {{Convert|300|km/h|0|abbr=on}}.\n\nDimensions are L x W  x H: 4830mm (190.15&nbsp;in) x 2000mm (78.74&nbsp;in) x 1285mm (50.59&nbsp;in), with a wheelbase of 2760mm (108.66&nbsp;in).\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable mw-collapsible\"\n|+\n!engine\n!displacement\n!bore/stroke\n!compression\n!induction\n!hp(kw)/rpm\n!torque Nm(lb\u00b7ft)\n!0\u2013100&nbsp;km/h (0-62 mph)\n|-\n|LS3\n| 6,162 cc (6.162 L; 376.0 cu in)\n|4.06 in (103&nbsp;mm) bore and 3.62 in (92mm) stroke\n|10.7:1\n|N/A\n|450&nbsp;bhp(335&nbsp;kW)/5900\n|585(424&nbsp;lb\u00b7ft)\n|3.9 sec\n|-\n|LS7\n|7,011 cc (7.011 L; 427.8 cu in)\n|4.125in (104.775mm) bore and 4.00in (101.6mm) stroke\n|11.1:1\n|N/A\n|530&nbsp;bhp(395&nbsp;kW)/6300\n|650(452&nbsp;lb\u00b7ft)\n|3.5 sec\n|-\n|LS9\n| 6,162 cc (6.162 L; 376.0 cu in)\n|4.06 in (103&nbsp;mm) bore and 3.62 in (92&nbsp;mm) stroke\n|9.1:1\n|supercharged\n|650&nbsp;bhp(484&nbsp;kW)/6300\n|820(604&nbsp;lb\u00b7ft)\n|3.0 sec\n|}\n<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://jalopnik.com/the-sin-r1-gt-is-what-a-lotus-exige-would-be-with-an-ls-1679003105|title=The Sin R1 GT Is What A Lotus Exige Would Be With An LS3 V8|last=Petr\u00e1ny|first=M\u00e1t\u00e9|newspaper=Jalopnik|language=en-US|access-date=2017-01-09}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n[[Category:Cars of Bulgaria]]\n\n\n{{car-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{One source|date=May 