{"title_page": "Fiona Bell", "text_new": "{{BLP sources|date=April 2020}}\n{{Short description|Scottish actress}}\n{{Infobox person\n| name         = Fiona Bell \n| image        = \n| caption      = \n| birth_name   = \n| birth_date   =\n| birth_place  = [[Rosneath]],[[Argyll and Bute]], Scotland\n| occupation   = Actress\n| years_active = 1988\u2013present\n| spouse       = [[Conor Mullen]]\n| children     = 4\n| alma mater   = [[Royal Conservatoire of Scotland|Royal Scottish Academy of Music and Drama]]\n| television   = ''[[Soldier Soldier]]'' <br> ''[[Shetland (TV series)|Shetland]]'' <br> ''[[The Nest (British TV series)|The Nest]]''\n}}\n\n'''Fiona Bell''' is a Scottish actress, known for her role as Sergeant Angela McLeod on the [[BBC One|BBC]] drama series ''[[Soldier Soldier]]'' (1997-1998), as Donna Killick on the [[BBC One|BBC]] crime drama series ''[[Shetland (TV series)|Shetland]]'' (2018) and as Hilary on the ''[[BBC One|BBC]]'' drama series ''[[The Nest (British TV series)|The Nest]]'' (2020)<ref>{{cite news |title=Meet the cast of BBC One\u2019s The Nest, 12 April 2020 |url=https://www.radiotimes.com/news/tv/2020-04-12/the-nest-cast/ |publisher=Radio Times}}</ref>.\n\n==Early Life==\nBell was born in [[Rosneath]] on the island of [[Argyll and Bute]], [[Scotland]]. From an early childhood she took an interest in acting and joined the [[Scottish Youth Theatre]], [[Glasgow]] at the age of 15. She graduated from the [[Royal Conservatoire of Scotland|Royal Scottish Academy of Music and Drama]]<ref>{{cite news |title=RCS Alumni to watch this weekend |url=https://www.rcs.ac.uk/rcsathome/rcs-alumni-to-watch-this-weekend/ |accessdate=20 April 2020 |publisher=RCS}}</ref> with a BA Acting degree in 1986.\n\n==Personal Life==\nBell is married to Irish actor [[Conor Mullen]] who she met on the set of ''[[Soldier Soldier]]'' in 1991. She moved to [[Ireland]] in 1997 to get married and lives in [[Howth]], [[County Dublin]] with her husband and their four children. <ref>{{cite news |title=Conor Mullen - Biography |url=https://www.hellomagazine.com/profiles/conor-mullen/ |accessdate=20 April 2020 |publisher=Hello Magazine}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |title=Fiona Bell: 'Our daughter was shocked - her daddy was kissing a woman on stage - she stared straight over at me, 3 October 2016 |url=https://www.independent.ie/life/fiona-bell-our-daughter-was-shocked-her-daddy-was-kissing-a-woman-on-stage-she-stared-straight-over-at-me-35093448.html |accessdate=20 April 2020 |publisher=Independant.ie}}</ref>.\n\n==Career==\n\n===Film===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|- \n! Year\n! Title\n! Role\n! class=\"unsortable\" | Notes\n|-\n| 1996\n| ''[[Trainspotting (film)|Trainspotting]]''\n| Diane's Mother\n| \n|-\n| 1999\n| ''[[Gregory's Two Girls]]''\n| Maddy Underwood\n| \n|-\n| 2003\n| ''[[AfterLife (film)|Afterlife]]''\n| Lucy\n|\n|-\n| 2020\n| ''Finding You''\n| Nora\n| ''post-production\n|}\n\n===Television===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|- \n! Year\n! Title\n! Role\n! class=\"unsortable\" | Notes\n|-\n| 1995\n| ''[[The Bill]]''\n| Jackie Laine\n| Episode: Memorial\n|-\n| 1996\n| ''[[Screen One]]''\n| Maggie\n| Episode: Truth or Dare\n|-\n| 1996-1997\n| ''[[Soldier Soldier]]''\n| Sergeant Angela McCleod AGC\n| (Series 6-7)\n|-\n| 1999\n| ''[[Casualty (TV series)|Casualty]]''\n| April Spencer\n| Episode: To Have and to Hold\n|-\n| 1999\n| ''[[Taggart]]''\n| Francesca\n| Episodes: Fearful Lightning & A Fistful Of Chips\n|-\n| 2000\n| ''The Creatives''\n| Joanna\n| Episode: By The Way\n|-\n| 2000\n| ''[[Doctors (2000 TV series)|Doctors]]''\n| D.C. Jane Lynch\n| Episode: A Matter of Community\n|-\n| 2000\n| ''[[City Central (TV series)|City Central]]''\n| Lou\n| Episode: Respect\n|-\n| 2002\n| ''Rockface''\n| Heather\n| Episode: #1.1\n|-\n| 2000-2002\n| ''[[Eastenders]]''\n| P.C. Elaine Monks\n|\n|-\n| 2003\n| ''[[The Eustace Bros.|The Eustace Brothers]]''\n| Angie\n| Episode: #1.1\n|-\n| 2004\n| ''[[Casualty (TV series)|Casualty]]''\n| M